SLS 26RS-819 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 13
BY SENATOR FOIL AND REPRESENTATIVE WILEY
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Designates Saturday, March 21, 2026, as World Down
Syndrome Day at the Louisiana State Capitol.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To designate Saturday, March 21, 2026, as World Down Syndrome Day at the Louisiana
3 State Capitol and commend the efforts of the Down Syndrome Awareness Group and
4 the various Buddy Walks occurring throughout the state.
5 WHEREAS, World Down Syndrome Day is observed annually, on March 21, to raise
6 awareness and celebrate the lives and achievements of individuals with Down syndrome, as
7 promoted by the National Down Syndrome Society (NDSS); and
8 WHEREAS, Down syndrome is a genetic condition that occurs when an individual
9 has a full or partial extra copy of chromosome 21, thus the significance of holding the event
10 on March 21, and said genetic condition can lead to developmental delays and intellectual
11 disabilities; and
12 WHEREAS, individuals with Down syndrome make valuable contributions to their
13 families, communities, and society, and deserve to be treated with dignity, respect, and equal
14 opportunity; and
15 WHEREAS, the Down Syndrome Awareness Group is a nonprofit organization in
16 Louisiana that works to support individuals with Down syndrome and their families through
17 advocacy, education, and community programs; and
18 WHEREAS, the Down Syndrome Awareness Group organizes an annual Buddy
