1 Walk in Baton Rouge on or about March 21, to celebrate World Down Syndrome Day and
2 promote inclusion and acceptance and education; and
3 WHEREAS, Buddy Walks are community events held across the state of Louisiana
4 to celebrate individuals with Down syndrome, promote acceptance and inclusion, and raise
5 funds for programs and services that support them and their families with, among other
6 things, swim lessons, vision care, legal services, summer camps, and scholarships; and
7 WHEREAS, the Buddy Walks provide an opportunity for individuals with Down
8 syndrome, their families, friends, and allies to come together, raise awareness, and advocate
9 for the rights and well-being of this community and have fun while doing so; and
10 WHEREAS, the Down Syndrome Awareness Group of Baton Rouge is hosting the
11 Baton Rouge Buddy Walk on Saturday, March 21, 2026, from 9:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m., less
12 than a thousand feet from the Louisiana State Capitol, and the public and the members of
13 this body are encouraged to participate by attending the event or one like it closer to home.
14 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
15 recognize Saturday, March 21, 2026, as World Down Syndrome Day at the Louisiana State
16 Capitol and commends the efforts of the Down Syndrome Awareness Group and the various
17 Buddy Walks occurring throughout the state in celebration of this important day.
18 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
19 president of the Down Syndrome Awareness Group.
